'''African Peoples Union''' (in [[French language|French]]: ''Union des Populations Africaines'') is a [[political party]] in [[Cameroon]] led by the Panafrican scholar Hubert Kamgang. The party was founded in 1996.

UPA is [[Panafrican]] and supports the creation of a '[[United States of Africa]]'.

