'''Diekirch communal council''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil communal de Diekirch}}) is the [[Local government|local council]] for the [[Communes of Luxembourg|commune]] of [[Diekirch]], in north-eastern [[Luxembourg]].
It consists of thirteen members, elected every six years by [[proportional representation]].<ref name="Conseil Communal">{{cite web |url=http://www.diekirch.lu/fr/administration/conseil |title=Le conseil communal |accessdate=2008-04-24 |date= |publisher=Commune of Diekirch |language=fr}}</ref> The [[Luxembourgian communal election, 2005|last elections]] were held on 9 October 2005, and resulted in a draw between the [[Christian Social People's Party]] (CSV) and the [[Luxembourg Socialist Workers' Party]] (LSAP). In the ''[[Collège échevinal (Luxembourg)|collège échevinal]]'', the CSV forms a coalition with [[The Greens (Luxembourg)|The Greens]], under the leadership of CSV [[Mayor of Diekirch|mayor]] [[Jacques Dahm]].<ref name="Conseil Communal" />
{| class="wikitable" ! colspan=2 width=300px| Party ! width=50px| Seats ! width=300px| Councillors |- | style="background-color: {{Christian Social People's Party/meta/color}}" | | valign=top| [[Christian Social People's Party]] (CSV) | valign=top| 5 | [[Robert Bohnert]], [[Paul Bonert]], [[Jacques Dahm]], [[Françoise Kerger-Faber]], [[Nico Michels]] |- | style="background-color: {{Luxembourg Socialist Workers' Party/meta/color}}" | | valign=top| [[Luxembourg Socialist Workers' Party]] (LSAP) | valign=top| 5 | René Blum, [[Emile Eischen]], [[Claude Haagen]], [[René Kanivé]], [[Claude Thill]] |- | style="background-color: {{The Greens (Luxembourg)/meta/color}}" | | valign=top| [[The Greens (Luxembourg)|The Greens]] | valign=top| 2 | [[Elisabeth Hoffmann]], [[Fränk Thillen]] |- | style="background-color: {{Democratic Party (Luxembourg)/meta/color}}" | | valign=top| [[Democratic Party (Luxembourg)|Democratic Party]] (DP) | valign=top| 1 | [[Ernest Breuskin]] |- | colspan=4 | <small>Source: [http://www.diekirch.lu/fr/administration/conseil Commune of Diekirch]</small> |}
Since the elections of October 2011, the composition of the council has changed. The socialist party LSAP has 7 members, CSV 3, DP 2, Déi Greng 1. The mayor is Claude Haagen (LSAP)
