h Algeria|French-Algerian]] [[Sociology|sociologist]] and [[anthropologist]]. She was also a former professor at [[Mouloud Mammeri University of Tizi-Ouzou|Tizi Ouzou University]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news | url = http://www.huffpostmaghreb.com/2014/11/20/fanny-colonna-sociologie-_n_6190728.html? | title = Disparition de la sociologue et anthropologue Fanny Colonna, une passionnée des Aurès | last = | first = | date = 20 November 2014 | work = Huffington Post | language = French | access-date = 25 February 2016 | via = }}</ref>
== Biography == Colonna was born in [[El Milia]], and was the daughter of a French [[Civil service|civil servant]] "who made sure she learned [[Arabic]]."<ref>{{Cite journal | last = Burke | first = Edmund III | date = 2015-05-01 | title = FANNY COLONNA (1934–2014) | url = http://journals.cambridge.org/article_S002074381500032X | journal = International Journal of Middle East Studies | volume = 47 | issue = 02 | pages = 417–419 | doi = 10.1017/S002074381500032X | issn = 1471-6380 }}</ref> Colonna lived in [[Algeria]] until 1993.<ref name=":0" /> She "established her reputation with a study of the Algerian schoolteacher class during the colonial period."<ref>{{Cite book | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=hHThx759I-kC&lpg=PA29&dq=%22fanny%20colonna%22&pg=PA29#v=onepage&q=%22fanny%20colonna%22&f=false | title = Culture, Identity, and Politics | last = Gellner | first = Ernest | publisher = Cambridge University Press | year = 1987 | isbn = 9780521336673 | location = | pages = }}</ref> Colonna also conducted an [[Ethnography|ethnographic]] study in the [[Aures, Algeria|Aures]] between 1970 and 1980.<ref>{{Cite web | url = http://iris.ehess.fr/index.php?396 | title = Fanny Colonna | last = | first = | date = | website = L'Iris | publisher = | language = French | access-date = 25 February 2016 }}</ref>
