{{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Turkey}} "Hani?" | image = | caption = | year = 1982 | country = Turkey | artist = [[:tr:Neco (şarkıcı)|Neco]] | as = | with = | language = Turkish | languages = | composer = Olcayto Ahmet Tuğsuz, Faik Tuğsuz | lyricist = Olcayto Ahmet Tuğsuz | conductor = [[Garo Mafyan]] | place = 15th | points = 20 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?1982tr from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Dönme Dolap | prev_link = Dönme Dolap | next = Opera (song) | next_link = Opera (song) }}
'''"Hani?"''' ("Where?") was the [[Turkey|Turkish]] entry in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1982]], performed in [[Turkish language|Turkish]] by [[:tr:Neco (şarkıcı)|Neco]].
The song was performed fifth on the night, following [[United Kingdom]]'s [[Bardo (band)|Bardo]] with "[[One Step Further]]" and preceding the [[Finland]]'s [[Kojo (singer)|Kojo]] with "[[Nuku pommiin]]". At the close of voting, it had received 20 points, placing 15th in a field of 18.
It was succeeded by [[Çetin Alp]] & [[The Short Waves]] with "[[Opera (song)|Opera]]" as the [[Turkey in the Eurovision Song Contest|Turkish representative]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1983|1983 contest]].
