The '''Neapolitani''' were an ancient people of [[Sardinia]], noted by [[Ptolemy]] (III, 3).  They dwelt south of the [[Scapitani]] and the [[Siculensi]] and north of the [[Solcitani]] and the [[Noritani]].  Their chief city was [[Neapolis, Sardinia|Neapolis]], located approximately 20&nbsp;km north of modern [[Guspini]].

